West Ham are keen to take Wilfried Zaha if Manchester United agree to let the 21-year-old leave. 

Zaha's future at United is in doubt after new manager Louis van Gaal said he only sees the England international as a striker in his new 3-5-2 formation. 

With Robin Van Persie, Wayne Rooney, Javier Hernandez and Danny Welbeck already established at Old Trafford, Van Gaal may allow Zaha to leave.

